line_2: Thought Nature taught to wed her kin,
Visits are pay'd: around are seen

line_1: By day, by night; the Myrtle ever-green,
line_2: Beneath whose shade Love holds his rites unseen;

line_1: Yet find thy swain — an ever-green.
line_2: Thy soul's unfading charms be seen;

line_1: Save the dark leaves of some rude ever-green,
line_2: No mark of vegetable life is seen,
